RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 28 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONIQUES DAREDEVIL raced off the pace up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the five path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. MAMBO DANCER dueled on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path, was caught in late stretch and kept on to the wire. DIXIELAND DANCER trailed the field early, saved ground around the turn and improved position in the stretch. DR. ANN dueled between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, dropped back while racing in the four path around the turn and faded further in the stretch. REAL DOOZIE dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the bend and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Two Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COX CANYON trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the five path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear in the final furlong. MY EAGLE SOARS tracked the leaders on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, dueled from the four path around the turn and in upper stretch, was caught by the winner late and kept on the wire. MR MURGO led the way through the early going, dueled from the three path around the bend and continued to battle to the finish, getting caught late and just missing second. HOP AND SCOTCH raced off the pace up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the five path and made no bid. DIXIEMAGIC chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three path and faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUNITA brushed with the horse to her outside at the break, led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and held her margin to the wire. UNCAPTURED DREAMS bumped mildly with the horse to her inside at the start, recovered to track the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the bend from the three path and chased on in the lane. REASONABLY LOVELY bumped lightly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, came around the turn in the five path and improved position in the stretch. MISS NEO trailed the field on the outside early, continued around the turn in the two path and passed tiring horses in the lane. CHIEF AGAIN chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and weakened in the stretch. KANEM raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and flattened out in the lane. JAZHARA bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 28 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIT BY A WAVE led the way on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn and pulled clear in the stretch. EXPRESS PHAROAH raced off the pace through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the five path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. ROYAL SQUEEZE chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the bend and kept on in the lane. BLAME BISHOP pressed the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. GOLOVKIN tracked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and was outkicked in the lane. MR LIGHTNING BOY was away from the gate slowly, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and was never a factor. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE FIVE, MR LIGHTNING BOY, HAD A FAIR START AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 5F Turf CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $75,000. Weight, 122 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND OAK (IRE) raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and drew off in the stretch. KERRY tracked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the bend from the four path and kept on to the finish. NINETY NINE trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and gained ground late. DAMASO chased the leaders between horses up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, and faded in the stretch. REDIFINED raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, began a bid from the five path coming around the bend and flattened out in the lane. MOTOWN MISCHIEF led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 106. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 29500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $100,000 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED IN 2022 - 2023. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 28 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $100,000 (Races Where Entered For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOPPER T brushed with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way racing in the two path around the turn and drew off in the stretch. NO QUE NO brushed with the horse to his inside at the start, stalked the pace setters on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the bend in the three path and chased the winner home in the lane. FIGURETI (CHI) raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and improved position in the lane. WHERE PARADISE LAY raced off the pace on the outside early, continued around the turn in the two path and never threatened. PERFECT SPEIGHTY chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and weakened in the lane. ABOUT TODAY (ARG) raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, moved up from the four path coming around the turn, faded in the stretch and was vanned off after crossing the wire. WICKED WARRIOR trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AXCEL trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and kicked clear late. I LIKE BOSTON bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, stalked the pace setters up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the four path and kept on in the lane. MYSPECIALVALENTINE led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the three path around the bend, was caught in midstretch and chased on to the wire. MOCCASIN BEND raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the stretch. FISHERMAN OSCAR bumped hard with the horse to his inside and was forced to check at the start, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and showed no kick. MIND FLAYER chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCESS TERESKA raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path coming around the turn, cut in upper stretch and pulled clear in the final furlong. FEEL LIKE GUESSING dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path coming around the bend, kicked clear in the lane and was caught late. RAIN OF BLESSING tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path, switched to the outside when PRINCESS TERESKA cut in near the eight pole and chased the winner home from there. SOLDAT TEMPTATION raced off the pace on the inside early, navigated the turn from the four path and improved position mildly in the stretch. TOOSWEETFORME dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the bend and weakened in the lane. SONGTELLER raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, dropped back from the two path coming around the turn and was empty in the stretch. FABULOUS PHILLY chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and faded in the lane. POLITICAL ASTRAY was reluctant to load, walked out of the gate, hopping up in the process and generally just getting away slowly, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and was not a factor. THE TRAINER OF HORSE SIX, RAIN OF BLESSING, FILED AN OBJECTION CITING INTERFERENCE AGAINST HORSE FIVE, PRINCESS TERESKA, IN UPPER STRETCH. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS ALSO MADE INTO THE START CONCERNING HORSE EIGHT, POLITICAL ASTRAY. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINSIH FOR EITHER INSTANCE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DORSODURO chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, challenged from the four path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. NOT A DANCE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the bend, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position late. HEAVY WEIGHT led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn and chased the top two home in the lane. GENESIS ONE stalked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the six path coming around the turn and was outkicked in the final furlong. MOCA MONSTER raced off the pace early, came around the turn in the three path and passed tiring horses in the lane while never truly threatening. RUM NOT BOURBON raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and never threatened. PERSONAL FINANCE tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the five path around the bend and faded in the stretch. MY WROTE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside in the early going, angled in to save ground around the turn and was empty from there. LOCKDOWN LOVER raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path and made no bid.
